3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper mentions the complexity of the encoding and decoding algorithms, which could be relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper mentions the error-correcting capability of the codes, which could be relevant to social and information networks. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper mentions the construction of codes over finite fields, which could be relevant to networking and internet architecture.
